summary:
I am Portuguese, 31 years old, lived in 2 countries outside Portugal, travel 21 countries and around 260 cities. 

I always like to challenge myself in different ways, learn different perspectives, innovate, interact and communicate. I align my intentions with my actions. I believe that I create my destiny.

I am self-motivated, passionate about traveling and inspired to make this a successful business.

I invest time passionately learning new skills, searching for new experiences and ways to bring new ideas to the market.

My background in software consultancy combined with ambition and enthusiasm resulted in establishing strong foundations for growth, innovation, and efficiency. With this, I can realize new business and products.

I worked one year at Schneider Electric in Paris like a Junior Enterprise Architect during my Double Master in Sorbonne University.

I worked during five years in SAS Institute Portugal like a consultant in Professional Sales Department focus on these areas:

- Business Intelligence;
- Customer Intelligence;
- Risk Intelligence;
- Pre-sales Activities;
- Trainer in SAS products.

